if any exception raises JVM will be taking care..its responsible for ArithmeticException i.e predefined

If any app, if i want my own exception like invalidTransactionException.. i.e my project require my own exception
E.g - InvalidAgeException-- user defined exception--user should create object
JVM can't handle user defined objects..so to handle user defined exception to JVM we need to use THROW keyword
now JVM is able to handle our exception

Two types of user defined exceptions

-->user defined checked--normal java class extends Exception
zero argumented constructor
parameterized constructor

e.g Exception in thread "main" javaLearning.exceptionHandling.RatanVideos.InvalidAgeException
	at javaLearning.exceptionHandling.RatanVideos.ThrowKeyWord.status(ThrowKeyWord.java:10)
	at javaLearning.exceptionHandling.RatanVideos.ThrowKeyWord.main(ThrowKeyWord.java:17)

user defined unchecked--normal java class extends RunTimeException
zero argumented constructor
parameterized constructor

process to write exceptions
create exception
use that exception in our project

Compiler always warns Checked exceptions so we have to handle checked exceptions by using try-catch or throws keyword
 
